# Model Architecture

## MotionGPT backbone (frozen)
- Freeze ALL parameters after loading: for p in backbone.parameters(): p.requires_grad = False
- Extract T5 decoder hidden states via register_forward_hook on last T5 decoder layer
- Extract T5 encoder output via hook (for LengthPredictor)
- LM head stays frozen and active — activation head runs in PARALLEL

## LengthPredictor
- Input: encoder_hidden [B, T_enc, 768] -> GlobalAvgPool -> [B, 768]
- Linear(768->128) -> GELU -> Dropout(0.1) -> Linear(128->1)
- Output: log(T_frame) as float [B, 1]
- Inference: T_frame = int(exp(pred).round().clamp(min_T, max_T))
- Init: Xavier uniform

## ActivationHead (cross-attention upsampler — NOT Conv1d)
- Keys/Values: T5 decoder hidden [B, T_tok, 768] projected via Linear(768->256)
- Queries: learned position embeddings [1, T_frame, 256] (T_frame from LengthPredictor)
- nn.MultiheadAttention(embed_dim=256, num_heads=4, batch_first=True)
- 3x nn.TransformerEncoderLayer(d_model=256, nhead=4, batch_first=True, dropout=0.1)
- Linear(256->80, bias=False) -> raw logits [B, T_frame, 80]
- Sigmoid applied OUTSIDE: BCEWithLogitsLoss during training; Sigmoid().clamp(0,1) at inference

## SVD warm-start (in model.py after loading backbone)
    W_lm = backbone.lm_head.weight.data  # [vocab_size, 768]
    _, _, Vt = torch.linalg.svd(W_lm, full_matrices=False)
    head.input_proj.weight.data.copy_(Vt[:256, :])  # [256, 768]

## LoRA (Stage 2 only)
- peft.LoraConfig(r=8, lora_alpha=16, lora_dropout=0.05, target_modules=["q", "v"])
- Apply to T5 decoder only
- Save with peft_model.save_pretrained("checkpoints/lora/")

## DDP rule (CRITICAL)
- DistributedDataParallel(activation_head, device_ids=[local_rank])
- MotionGPT backbone NOT wrapped in DDP
- Inference inside training loop: head_unwrapped = head.module if hasattr(head, 'module') else head
